==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Titanium
<hw>Ti*ta"ni*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. L.
<ets>Titani</ets> or <ets>Titanes</ets>, Gr. <?/, the sons of the
earth.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An elementary substance found
combined in the minerals manaccanite, rutile, sphene, etc., and isolated
as an infusible iron-gray amorphous powder, having a metallic luster. It
burns when heated in the air. Symbol Ti. Atomic weight 48.1.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Titano-</ent>⟦br⟧
